All Classes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Chat
    This is Chat class that models the behaviour of a Chat dialogue, the chat can be held between two users and each chat is uniquely identified by the combination of two users' id.
    ChatController
    This is a class which connects Chat model with Firestore database, the class is an intermediate to execute adding, deleting, updating, and getting operations of Chat objects from the Firestore
    Code
    This is Code class that models the behaviour of a Treasure Code, the Code can be scanned.
    CodeController
    This is controller class which connects Code model class with Firestore database, the CodeController class is an intermediate to execute adding, deleting, updating, and getting operations of User objects from the Firestore.
    DatabaseController  
    Invitation
    This is Invitation class that models the behaviour of a Invitation, the invitation is held by two users.
    InvitationController
    This is invitation controller class which connects Invitation model class with Firestore database, the InvitationController class is an intermediate to execute adding, deleting, updating, and getting operations of the Invitation objects from the Firestore.
    LocationMessage
    This is Location Message class which extends the Message class.
    Message
    This is Message class that models the a chatting message in a chat.
    Rank

    RankController
    This is rank controller class which connects Rank model class with Firestore database, the RankController class is an intermediate to execute adding, deleting, updating, and getting operations of the Rank objects from the Firestore.
